text: The Dwight D. Eisenhower Presidential Library and Museum is a presidential library created in honor of the 34th president of the United States, Dwight D. Eisenhower. It is located in Abilene, Kansas. The library also contains Eisenhower's grave and boyhood home. It was dedicated in 1963. ==Other websites== *Official Eisenhower Library website *The Eisenhower Presidential Library & Museum *Records of the General Services Administration regarding Eisenhower Presidential Center site acquisition, Dwight D.
